cmek_config_id.description: The unique id of the cmek config.

is_default.description: The default CmekConfig for the Customer.

kms_key.description: KMS key resource name which will be used to encrypt resources 'projects/{project}/locations/{location}/keyRings/{keyRing}/cryptoKeys/{keyId}'.

kms_key_version.description: KMS key version resource name which will be used to encrypt resources '<kms_key>/cryptoKeyVersions/{keyVersion}'.

last_rotation_timestamp_micros.description: The timestamp of the last key rotation.

location.description: The geographic location where the CMEK config should reside. The value can only be one of "us" and "eu".

name.description: The unique full resource name of the cmek config. Values are of the format 'projects/{project}/locations/{location}/cmekConfigs/{cmek_config_id}'. This field must be a UTF-8 encoded string with a length limit of 1024 characters.

notebooklm_state.description: Whether the NotebookLM Corpus is ready to be used.

set_default.description: Set the following CmekConfig as the default to be used for child resources if one is not specified. The default value is true.

kms_key.description: Single-regional kms key resource name which will be used to encrypt resources 'projects/{project}/locations/{location}/keyRings/{keyRing}/cryptoKeys/{keyId}'.

block.description: Single-regional CMEKs that are required for some VAIS features.
